Benedetto Varchi, Questione sull&lt;U+2019&gt;alchimia (Venice: 1544), page 54, in which Varchi claims that experimental tests of the equality of gravitational acceleration of bodies had been performed by a Dominican philosopher at Pisa, Francesco Beato, and by a Bolognese physician and botanist, Luca Ghini; the relevant passage is quoted and translated in: Charles B. Schmitt and Quentin Skinner, ed.s, The Cambridge History of Renaissance Philosophy (Cambridge, England: Cambridge University Press, 1988), page 222.↩
